description.narrative: Continued advocacy for quality early childhood education (ECE) and technical support including capacity building, developing guidelines, training resources, assessment tools; at national and state level has resulted in scale-up in 9 states (Assam, Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Gujarat, Maharashtra, Odisha, Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh and West Bengal), leveraging government resources. Nearly 539,000 trained anganwadi workers (AWW) are implementing developmentally appropriate curriculum, benefitting 7.2 million girls and boys (approx. 48% girls). In 33 focus districts in 14 states, 30% anganwadi centres (AWC) are delivering ECE service based on policy standards. In Maharashtra and Rajasthan 5000AWW organizing monthly counselling sessions for promoting responsive parenting | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
